                        "content": "The nurse is instructing a client to perform a testicular self-examination (TSE). The nurse would provide the client with which information about the procedure?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nThe TSE is recommended monthly after a warm bath or shower when the scrotal skin is relaxed. The client should stand to examine the testicles. Using both hands, with fingers under the scrotum and thumbs on top, the client needs to gently roll the testicles, feeling for any lumps.\n\nClient Needs: Health Promotion and Maintenance\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Testicles\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Cancer: Testicular\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Clinical Judgment, Health Promotion\nStrategies: Subject\n  Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, the procedure for performing TSE. Eliminate option 4 first because of the words 6 months. Next, eliminate option 3 because of the word one. From the remaining options, eliminate option 1 by trying to visualize the process of the self-examination.\n ",
                        "id": "1905164513f841d0bc01ed9edfd53311",
                        "mark": "0",
                        "collectionState": "0"
                    },
                    {
                        "optionList": [
                            {
                                "isRight": "1",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "7a9a5bf05b454db181a96d754602f5ab",
                                "content": "Do the exam on the same day every month."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "d39a7ae9cf6c4cf18d895fd6ba010b1c",
                                "content": "Do the exam 7 days after the start of the menstrual cycle."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "8f3758e4fc084b68a7f65146c24473e2",
                                "content": "Examine the left breast with the left hand and vice versa."
                            },
                            {
                                "isRight": "0",
                                "userAnswer": "",
                                "isSelected": "0",
                                "id": "56260f1eeabf4850ba0ee40f7cd401c8",
                                "content": "Use the tips of the fingers to increase the likelihood of feeling lumps."
