                        "content": "A group of postmenopausal women are learning to do breast self-examination (BSE) in a teaching session at the clinic. The clinic nurse would teach the group which point about this procedure?",
                        "subjectId": "ad5ab04c79144c0ea9b83385308c3b1d",
                        "difficultyIds": "a0f7d178f7b728b8bba7ef20ddeca62d",
                        "difficulty": "考试范围-Evaluating 评价",
                        "textAnalysis": "Rationale:\nWomen who are postmenopausal are taught to do BSE on the same day every month. Before menopause, women would do the procedure 7 days after the start of the menstrual cycle, when the breasts are least tender. Each breast is examined with the opposite hand. The pads of the fingers, not the fingertips, would be used for palpation. The client may use a circular, up and down, or wedge method of assessment. Consistency of use of the same method is more important than the actual method used.\n\nClient Needs: Health Promotion and Maintenance\nClinical Judgment/Cognitive Skill(s): Take Action\nCognitive Ability: Applying\nContent Area: Health Assessment/Physical Exam: Breasts\nHealth Problem: Adult Health: Cancer: Breast\nIntegrated Process: Teaching and Learning\nPriority Concepts: Health Promotion, Patient Education\nStrategies: Subject\n   Test-Taking Strategy:\nFocus on the subject, BSE. Note the word postmenopausal. This tells you that the correct option is the assessment technique that is appropriate for this population. With this in mind, eliminate option 2 first. Visualize this assessment technique to correctly choose among the remaining options.\n \n   ",
